 MBOMBELA: Amputee walkers Paul Steyn and Mike Minnie are walking from Pretoria to Cape Town to raise money for the Paul Steyn Foundation. This foundation helps to provide prostheses for those in need who are not able to afford them. The pair arrived in Kaapsehoop on Thursday and made their way to Mbombela on Friday where they were welcomed at i’langa Mall. READ ALSO:VIDEO: Lowveld Walkers welcomed back in Mbombela They will be leaving Mbombela on Tuesday after a speech at Protea Hotel along with finalists of the Mrs Mpumalanga competition. To view their full schedule or to contribute to their cause, go to the website www.paulsteynfoundation.org.za. READ ALSO: One local’s drive inspires many to hit the road See the videos of their arrival in Mbombela as well as the highlights of their journey thus far below: (function(d, s, id) {  var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];  if (d.getElementById(id)) return;  js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;  js.src = 'https://connect.facebook.net/en_GB/sdk.js#xfbml=1&version=v3.0';  fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);}(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk')); (function(d, s, id) {  var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];  if (d.getElementById(id)) return;  js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;  js.src = 'https://connect.facebook.net/en_GB/sdk.js#xfbml=1&version=v3.0';  fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);}(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));